SIMPLE: marc
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marc
<hw>Marc</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>The
refuse matter which remains after the pressure of fruit, particularly of
grapes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marc</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Marc
<hw>Marc</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>marc</ets>; akin to G.
<ets>mark</ets>, Icel. <ets>m⟦oum⟧rk</ets>, perh. akin to E.
<ets>mark</ets> a sign. ⟦root⟧106, 273.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>mark</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A weight of various
commodities, esp. of gold and silver, used in different European
countries. In France and Holland it was equal to eight ounces.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A coin formerly current in England and Scotland,
equal to thirteen shillings and four pence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A German coin and money of account. See
<er>Mark</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marcantant</ent>⟦br⟧
